  "body": "The description of quarkus.hibernate-orm.statistics is not reflecting the reality.\r\n\r\nThe description here:\r\nhttps://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/0ae0c6c13e4a44e17194ccaf77c3edf00551b9a4/extensions/hibernate-orm/deployment/src/main/java/io/quarkus/hibernate/orm/deployment/HibernateOrmConfig.java#L38\r\n\r\nDoes not match the boolean condition:\r\nhttps://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/0ae0c6c13e4a44e17194ccaf77c3edf00551b9a4/extensions/hibernate-orm/deployment/src/main/java/io/quarkus/hibernate/orm/deployment/HibernateOrmProcessor.java#L1017\r\n\r\nIf hibernateOrmConfig.metricsEnabled is true, then the statistics property is completley ignored.\r\nTherefor setting statistics to false is not disabling statistics. \r\n\r\nI think this is wrong and should be changed to be allowed to disable statistics logging even if metrics are enabled and to match the description. This is polluting logs in production environments.\r\n\r\nThis affects the current master and Quarkus 2.2.3.Final\r\n",
